,Recommended,306040,17546791,"Posted: 15 August, 2015",all,Minzoku Bokumetsu,"I got this game for $.19, and it was worth every penny! There are 16 stages, so at a little over a cent each, great value!In all seriousness, though, The Howler is an interesting take on the old Lunar Lander game mechanic, but in addition to ""hold button to go up"", there is also the added challenge of navigating the effects of wind on your hot air balloon, which does get a bit frustrating when the slightest thing will literally make you a splode. There's also a ""voice"" option where you can blow into your microphone instead of clicking the mouse, but that feels like more hot air than I really need for one game.The biggest lesson from The Howler is a hot air balloon is the worst vehicle for precision maneuvering. At least the artwork is gorgeous, though."
