,Not Recommended,306040,19343600,"Posted: 28 November, 2015",all,Chef Excellence,"The Howler is a beautiful but whisper-thin sort of puzzle game that'll provide you with about an hour of entertainment. You pilot a balloon through a very nicely handpainted 2D representation of Vilnius, Lithuania, done up all steampunk-like. You press the mouse button to provide thrust which carries the balloon higher—steering is left up to the winds which're denoted on the side of the screen. Using those winds you steer around, over, and under obstacles and enemies to reach your goal, which always consists of picking up and/or dropping off items before plopping down on a landing pad elsewhere in the level.That's really it. Lunar Lander with some extra physics. There's a story attached involving impending riots and your efforts to stave them off supposedly taken from or relating in some way to the Lithuanian novelHour of the Wolf, but like the rest of the game it's pretty insubstantial.There's also an option to use your PC's microphone to control the balloon with your voice, which I didn't use at all. One, it feels like a bit of a gimmick which I don't consider to be either innovative or even essential to gameplay. If the voice commands were integrated into the experience in some way that made them inseperable—or even more effective than just clicking the mouse—I might take the concept seriously, but it seems more like the developer asking you to handicap yourself to make its game seem deeper than it really is. You can play Snake with a Dance Dance Revolution pad, but that doesn't make it innovative, it's still just Snake. Two, I have roommates.All that said the levels are well designed—occasionally cunningly so—and it is very well presented with lovely artwork and music, giving the game a cohesive style that kept me relatively engrossed for the 58 minutes it lasted.I picked this up for $0.49 during the Autumn Sale. For the cost of a game of pinball I suppose I have nothing to cry about. But it normally retails for $1.99, and there's simply not enough here to recommend even at that price."
,Recommended,306040,19419622,"Posted: 1 December, 2015",all,mathead,"The Howler is a simple, nice looking game of skill where you take advantage of air stream to pilot a hot air balloon over obstacles. It's very obviously a direct port from tablet but it works fine on PC, even though it only offers one screen resolution that will display the game in a dark frame. This is the game to challenge your grandma who would otherwise never touch a videogame. It's very cheap and often even cheaper on sales, so there's really no risk at throwing a handful of cents at it."
