,Recommended,306040,22850836,"Posted: 7 May, 2016",all,ShandyAndy,"The HowlerThis review was last edited after I had completed the first 15 levelsShort ReviewA delightful game with beautiful, hand drawn graphics & simple game play that whilst only mildly challenging is fun to play none the less.Long ReviewThere is no tutorial but adequate hints are provided in the first few levels and the game play is so simple the lack of a tutorial is not an issue.The game is set in 2D with beautiful, hand drawn graphics. The game play is simple. You control a got air balloon that you must direct from one point to another, performing simple tasks like dropping off parcels along the way. The audio is restricted to sound effects which are fairly limited but effective.The controls are simple, for vertical control you press the left mouse button to ignite the hot air and raise and stop pressing it to allow gravity to take over. For left and right control you must rely on the wind direction and speed which varies at different altitudes and is indicated by an arrow on the left hand side; the number of feathers in the quill indicating the strength. Thus you need to be at the correct altitude to move in the correct direction. The SPACE BAR is used to drop objects you are carrying and there is a pause button click able by the mouse.You cannot pan around so you only see a screens worth of the level around the current location of the balloon. If you go too high, low, left or right and disappear off the edge of the level you die. Similarly if the balloon hits other objects you will usually die.As you progress through levels additional obstacles like floating bombs are introduced. Fortunately these move in a predictable manner.The only way to play is via a campaign of different screen levels you play in order (although once you have completed a level you can replay it at any time). The levels are pretty small (maybe twice the width of the monitor).When you start a new level you are quickly shown what needs to be done by the camera panning about and short text messages appearing. You have a set time limit to complete the tasks.This game play is short and the game can be easily be completed in 2-3 hours. Ignore my 17 hours game play - I left the game running in the start menu overnight by mistake.ProsBeautiful, hand drawn graphicsSimple game playConsThe sequence at the start of a level to show you what to do moves along a little fast for me to read all of the textMarks Out Of 55) Must have - stop whatever you're playing now and play this4) Worth the asking price and considering as your next purchase3) Maybe purchase if you're stuck for choosing your next game or mildly discounted2) Only purchase if it is heavily discounted1) Not worth getting even if given away freeWhere I got the game fromI have no idea how this game got into my Steam library but boy am I glad it did!Platform Played OnIntel Pentium G3258 Anniversary Edition, 8Gb RAM, Palit GTX 750, Windows 10, EasyAcc Mouse and Steelseries Merc keyboardMy best guess for a  PEGI Rating3: I can't see any reason to raise it above this.PEGI Ratings"
