76561198119604102,Recommended,306040,20096309,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,Shaost,"The Howler, a game where you can scream as loud as your heart desires, and to this day, the only game (which I have played) where actually screaming of rage, can help you pass a level.Graphics - Wow, just wow, every single thing here is hand drawn. Only by the sheer amount of detail, you know that those guys who did this, really poured their hearts into it. And once again for the painters wow. 9/10Music - Deep and mysterious, it just adds to the whole aesthetic to the game, which itself is deep and mysterious. 7/10Story - Couldn't quite understand the story, because it is mostly given to you by little chunks of story, at the start of every level. That is probably done to not spoil the book it is based of off/on, yes you heard right, a book. ''Hour of the Wolf'' by Andrius B. Tapinas. (Now I don't know, if I can post links which are not directly connected to steam, I may be mistaken) You can find the book on Amazon, for a pretty cheap price I might add. (The score is based on playing only the GAME, it may change when I get and read the book.) 5/10Content - A few levels, but as you progress through the game, more and more mechanics are unlocked, which make every single new level, something new to be experienced. 7/10Controls - Done by the mouse or your own voice, or any sound that you make, be that bashing your head on the desk (don't do that) or by breaking every single bone in your body (or that). Press and hold to go up, let go to go down or scream to go up, don't scream to go down. Just by having the option of using sound as a way to control the game, it gets an easy 8/10.Gameplay - Simple, but effective. Also well paced, but I do warn you, some levels need a little bit more thinking to get through. Remember, if what you are doing does not work, try and think of a solution, rather than raging. Also I have a little pro tip for the game, to stop getting your blump to go up from the sound, just unplug your microphone. I know genius. 7/10A really well made game. Bonus points for making the game small, which in contrast makes the players want to read the book, to understand the story, really well thought out. Also I do encourage people who liked the game, to give the book a try, this is not from a person who has read the book, but from a person who will most definitely read it. Also on a side note, it does not hurt to read overall.Final Score: 7.2/10"
