76561198018618204,Not Recommended,306040,29019237,Posted: 4 January,all,Nihis,"A poorly madeartsyflashAs proud as i am, that my own countrymen managed to create a game, that portrays my city of birth in such a elegant steampunk-ish fashion, i cannot force myself to shake the thought the this was the main concern of the developer, as the gameplay mechanics are very frustrating and the game requires a way too high level of precision and in most cases - luck to complete the levels. Furthermore, i've noticed how the game is a cross-ad for A.Tapinas' book Hour of the wolf, that shares it's name with a swedish horror drama that i enjoyed far more than this game and the book combined.Pros and cons+ Gorgeus artstyle+ Decent soundtrack+- Simple concept- Frustratingly difficult due to poor level design- Poorly optimized for screens wider than those of smartphones, resulting in low res, or the game being displayed in a small cube, with black outlines taking up most of the space, letting the player believe, that the game is in""fullscreen""- Short* Useless functions/alternative controls like voice command, which are nowhere close to being precise enough for the game's sadistic needs.Vistiek norėčiau padėkot kūrėjam, kad skyrė laiko šiam projektui, nes visgi, kaip pirmas blynas, neturint patirties žaidimų kūrimo sferoje, tikrai ne baisiai prisvilęs."
